HEADWORD: Yarwhip
<hw>Yar"whip`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from its
sharp cry uttered when taking wing.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
European bar-tailed godwit; -- called also <altname>yardkeep</altname>,
and <xex>yarwhelp</xex>. See <er>Godwit</er>.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
